  <sharedProfiles>
    <profile name="Legio Custodes" typeId="d5a9-9164-1e30-7a35" typeName="Traits" hidden="false" id="c717-38ae-cee2-19f7">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="d5eb-0b8b-0f26-6233"/>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Golden Exemplar" typeId="d5a9-9164-1e30-7a35" typeName="Traits" hidden="false" id="ac3d-8bec-254d-3c8b">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="d5eb-0b8b-0f26-6233">If an Army&apos;s Primary Detachment is from the Legio Custodes Army List, the Controlling Player gains one additional Reaction Point if the Army contains any Models with the Golden Exemplar Trait.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="The Blade Splits" typeId="c14c-ecfd-ea65-58c9" typeName="Reaction" hidden="false" id="b9c9-67dc-715f-74a7">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="5d02-0e54-0f6a-0f0b">This Reaction allows the Reacting Unit to split into two new Units when an enemy Unit ends its move within 12&quot;.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Trigger" typeId="02e4-3f90-3125-f8b4">Once per Battle, the Reactive Player may declare a The Blade Splits Advanced Reaction in Step 2 of the Move Sub-Phase process, if an enemy Unit ends a move within 12&quot; and Line of Sight of a Unit under the Reactive Player&apos;s Control.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Cost" typeId="954a-972f-5c94-2ede">The Reactive Player must spend 1 point of their Reaction Allotment to declare a The Blade Splits Advanced Reaction, this cost paid as soon as the declaration is made.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Target" typeId="e102-8fdd-9cd4-c0f9">The Target Unit is always the Unit whose Move triggered the Advanced Reaction. Once the cost has been paid, the Reactive Player must select one Unit under their control that is within 12&quot; and has Line of Sight to the Target Unit, and which contains only Models with the Legio Custodes and The Sodality Traits, and which also contains at least six Models. That Unit is the Reacting Unit.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Process" typeId="57cf-1c68-a020-2529">1. Once the The Blade Spits Advanced Reaction has been declared, the Active Player must completely resolve the Target Unit&apos;s Movement.
2. Once the Target Unit has finished its move, the Reactive Player must move a number of Models from the Reacting Unit. When making this move, the Reactive Player must move at least three Models from the Reacting Unit a number of inches up to the Base Value of each Model&apos;s Initiative Characteristic so that they are no longer in Unit Coherency with the rest of the Reacting Unit, but are in Unit Coherency with each other. Once this movement is complete, there must still be at least three Models from the Reacting Unit which did not move and which are still in Unit Coherency with each other.
3. Once this movement has been resolved, the Models from the Reacting Unit which moved are considered to form a new Unit separate from the rest of the Reacting Unit for all purposes, including the scoring of Victory Points (excluding the Last Man Standing (X) Secondary Objective). All Models which were in the Reacting Unit when The Blade Splits Advanced Reaction was declared are considered to have made a Reaction in this Player Turn.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Raptor&apos;s Surge" typeId="9b5f-da4e-5739-cbcf" typeName="Gambit:" hidden="false" id="f484-f6c7-0361-fed0">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="98f3-41cf-e3be-2ae7">This Gambit grants a Model additional attacks based on the number of enemy Models in the Combat from which the Model was selected.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="2d7d-b1d9-dead-605a">If this Gambit is selected, then if the Opposing Player may claim a greater Outside Support Bonus in the Focus Step than the Controlling Player, the Model for which it was selected gains a bonus to its current Attacks Characteristic in the following Strike Step equal to the difference in the Outside Support Bonuses the Players could claim for the Challenge, to a maximum of +3.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Heaven&apos;s Strike" typeId="9b5f-da4e-5739-cbcf" typeName="Gambit:" hidden="false" id="e420-6f61-30cb-98b0">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="98f3-41cf-e3be-2ae7">This Gambit halves a Model&apos;s Attacks Characteristic but replaces the Critical Hit (6+) Special Rule with Critical Hit (5+) on its Weapons.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="2d7d-b1d9-dead-605a">If this Gambit is selected, then as long as the Model for which it was selected is declared to be using a Weapon with the Critical Hit (6+) Special Rule at the beginning of the Focus Step, that Special Rule is replaced with the Critical Hit (5+) Special Rule and that Model&apos;s Base Attacks Characteristic is halved for the duration of the Strike Step.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Stone&apos;s Aegis" typeId="9b5f-da4e-5739-cbcf" typeName="Gambit:" hidden="false" id="d7a4-c4a2-dbfc-0f54">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="98f3-41cf-e3be-2ae7">This Gambit modifies a Model&apos;s Toughness by +1 but causes Wound Tests made for it to fail on a 1 or 2.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="2d7d-b1d9-dead-605a">This Gambit may only be selected for a Model with the &apos;Shield&apos; Trait. If this Gambit is selected, then the Model for which it was selected gains a +1 modifier to its Toughness Characteristic for the duration of the Strike Step, but any Wound Tests made for that Model in the same Strike Step automatically fail on a natural result of 1 or 2.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="World Serpent&apos;s Bane" typeId="9b5f-da4e-5739-cbcf" typeName="Gambit:" hidden="false" id="49cc-971f-80f7-e46f">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="98f3-41cf-e3be-2ae7">This Gambit limits a Model to one attack but sets that attack&apos;s Damage Characteristic to the Model&apos;s remaining wounds.</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="2d7d-b1d9-dead-605a">If this Gambit is selected, the Model for which is was selected may only make a single attack in the following Strike Step regardless of its Attacks Characteristic, but the Damage Characteristic of the Weapon used to make that attack is modified to be equal to the Model&apos;s current Wounds Characteristic while that attack is resolved.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
  </sharedProfiles>
</catalogue>
